p: The second compound for relative abundance was the 1,8-cineole. It was present in 25 genotypes and the highest percentage was 43.26% in the candidate clone V4. Other compounds with high relative abundance were α-terpinyl acetate with the maximum of 23.56% in RUB95, methyleugenol with 19.66% in the sample LAC11, linalool with 35.10% in ISL3, α-terpineol with 23.21% in the RUM14 genotype, β-caryophyllene with 35.00% in MON5, α-humulene with 24.72% in LAC31, Trans-caryophyllene oxide with 25.69% in ORO2, and humulene epoxide II with 15.43% in ISL1.
